<H2>_cmnd(NurbsSurface) must have a surface type of  GL_MAP2_VERTEX_3</H2><PRE>

</PRE>
<H2>or  GL_MAP2_VERTEX_4.  To mark the end of the NURBS surface defi­</H2><PRE>
nition, call _cmnd(EndSurface).  Trimming of  NURBS  surfaces  is
supported  with  _cmnd(BeginTrim),  _cmnd(PwlCurve),  _cmnd(Nurb­
sCurve), and _cmnd(EndTrim). See the  _cmnd(BeginTrim)  reference
page  for  details.   GL  evaluators are used to render the NURBS
surface as a set of polygons.  Evaluator state is preserved  dur­

</PRE>
<H2>ing  rendering  with  _glcmnd(PushAttrib)(GL_EVAL_BIT) and _glcm­</H2><PRE>
nd(PopAttrib)().  See the _glcmnd(PushAttrib) reference page  for
details  on exactly what state these calls preserve.  The follow­
ing commands render a textured NURBS surface  with  normals;  the
texture  coordinates and normals are also described as NURBS sur­
faces:

gluBeginSurface(nobj);
   gluNurbsSurface(nobj, ..., GL_MAP2_TEXTURE_COORD_2);
   gluNurbsSurface(nobj, ..., GL_MAP2_NORMAL);
   gluNurbsSurface(nobj,   ...,   GL_MAP2_VERTEX_4);   gluEndSur­
face(nobj);

_cmnd(BeginCurve),   _cmnd(BeginTrim),   _cmnd(NewNurbsRenderer),
_cmnd(NurbsCurve), _cmnd(NurbsSurface), _cmnd(PwlCurve)






























